29/12/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Supreme Election Board announced on Sunday (December 28th) the official timetable ahead of the March 29th local elections. Voter registry lists will be on display between January 5th and January 30th. A drawing of lots to determine the order in which political parties' names appear on paper ballots will take place on January 24th. Lists of candidates will become public on March 1st, followed by campaigning between March 19th and March 28th. A recent poll found that public support for Turkey's opposition parties is growing, while the ruling Justice and Development Party is losing ground. (Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, Xinhua - 28/12/08)
